[Data by country, area, or territory for 26 Aug 2022 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2022%20WHO%20Data%20Tables%2026%20Aug%202022_1661655130.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 22.8% of cases and 50.7% of deaths during the past 24 hours. It has reported more than 175.01 million cases, 2nd to the European region as the most severely affected region. The USA (124 151) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Brazil, Chile, Peru, Puerto Rico, Guatemala, Honduras and Bolivia.

- The European region reported 20.7% of cases and 16.6% of deaths over the last 24 hours. It is the most affected region, with cumulative cases exceeding 246.72 million. Many countries did not report cases in the last 24 hours or longer including Germany, the UK, Turkey, Spain, Ukraine, and Greece. A total of 15 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 4 countries reporting more than 10 000 and 11 reporting over 1000 cases, while 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported no cases or deaths over the last 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 22.94 million cases.

- The African region reported 0.79% of cases and 6 deaths during the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.27 million cases. Réunion (5711) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Mayotte. The remaining countries did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 53.3% of daily case numbers and 26.8% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 82.56 million cases. Japan (227 139) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by South Korea, China, Australia, Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, New Zealand, and Singapore.

- The South East Asia region reported 2.3% of cases and 5.4% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 59.93 million cases. India (10 256) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Indonesia (4549) and Thailand (2062). Sri Lanka, Bhutan, and Maldives, among others, have not reported cases over the last many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 26 Aug 2022, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

