[In the past 24 hours, 13 countries: Japan (423 767), the USA (125 330), South Korea (95 538), Germany (33 226), Russia (46 452), Taiwan (26 718), Canada (22 884), Italy (21 995), Brazil (18 270), France (18 116), Georgia (12 595), India (11 860), and Australia (11 482) reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases. A global total of 3323 deaths were reported in the preceding 24 hours (25-26 Aug 2022).

A total of 39 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 22 of the 39 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 2 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the Western Pacific region, 3 are from the South East Asia region, and none from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 4.1%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 12.7%. Comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 7.6% decrease in daily reported cases and a 2.9% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 0.98 million newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 605.09 million cumulative reported cases and more than 6.48 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA

